- Poor drainage can cause problems such as ponding on the roadway, erosion aroundabutments, and early deterioration of structural members.
- Collecting the runoff and transporting it away from the bridge can prevent most of the problems, thus reducing future maintenance and rehabilitations costs.
- Proper geometrics during the preliminary stage is essential in order to accomplish this.
- The Bridge and Structures Office recommends placing the bridge deck drainage off of the structure.
- All expansion joints shall be watertight.
- Bridges shall have sufficient transverse and longitudinal slopes to allow the water to run quickly to the drains.
