PROMPT 67: What does MUTCD specify for pedestrian signal walk interval timing?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- A pedestrian change interval consisting of a flashing UPRAISED HAND (symbolizing DONT WALK) signal indication shall begin immediately following the WALKING PERSON (symbolizing WALK) signal indication. Following the pedestrian change interval, a buffer interval consisting of a steady UPRAISED HAND (symbolizing DONT WALK) signal indication shall be displayed for at least 2 seconds prior to the release of any conflicting vehicular movement. The sum of the time of the pedestrian change interval and the buffer interval shall not be less than the calculated pedestrian clearance time (seeParagraphs 7 through 16 of this Section). The buffer interval shall not begin later than the beginning of the red clearance interval, if used.^^^2^^^

